	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64121415"><p>Where it <i>is</i> used effectively, you won't notice.
</p><p>You don't know that that logo, image, or whatever was generated and saved somebody hours. You just see it.
</p><p>You don't know that generated code saved hours of some tedious refactoring, or implementing an API, or whatever, enabling a programmer to do in 2 hours what would have taken him 20 hours. It passed the programmer's review, automated testing, human testing, etc. and it saved him a lot of time overall. But how would you know that?
</p><p>You'll know when you see evidence of it <i>not</i> working though.</p></div>
